<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.00/1–2948: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-30T16:00:00-05:00">January
                                    30, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>297. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 515 rptd London as 61.<note n="1" xml:id="d387fn1">Dated January 29, <ref target="#pg_613">p.
                                    613</ref>.</note> Dept increasingly concerned by atmosphere of
                            crisis prevailing in Paris and its disintegrating effects on coalition.
                            Your talk with Blum approved. Do not hesitate approach Blum again or
                            other leaders whose parties show signs of bolting whenever you feel this
                            action would be salutary.</p>
                        <p>Gallman may wish indicate in proper quarters our concern lest things get
                            out of hand in Paris at this time.</p>
                        <p>Sent Paris as 297; rptd London as 317.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>